<doc id="54945" wikidata="Q2592664" url="?curid=54945" title="Ebenales">
<text>Ebenales is an order of flowering plants. This order was recognized in several systems, for example the Bentham &amp; Hooker system and the Engler system, although the Wettstein system preferred the name Diospyrales&#x27;. In the 1981 version of the Cronquist system it was an order placed in subclass Dilleniidae with the following :

*order Ebenales
*: family Ebenaceae
*: family Sapotaceae
*: family Styracaceae
*: family Symplocaceae

In the APG II system all the plants involved are assigned to the hugely expanded order &quot;Ericales&quot;.

